    "body": "## Summary\n- improve int4 GEMM lowering by removing the obsolete sub-byte MMA path and consolidating the active TensorCore emitter flow\n- add packed int4 buffer load/store helpers and wire the CUDA codegen path to handle packed int4 local/shared access more consistently\n- extend int4 MMA support in the CUDA templates and simplify the example and intrinsic utilities around the new path\n\n## Validation\n- `ruff check tilelang/intrinsics/mma_macro_generator.py tilelang/intrinsics/utils.py tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_mma.py examples/gemm_int4/example_tilelang_gemm_int4.py`\n- `python -m compileall tilelang/intrinsics/mma_macro_generator.py tilelang/intrinsics/utils.py tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_mma.py examples/gemm_int4/example_tilelang_gemm_int4.py`\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * INT4 GEMM example: correctness test with input packing, configurable threads, and optional CUDA kernel preview.\n  * CUDA device helpers and runtime support for packed 4-bit (INT4/UINT4) buffer load/store.\n  * INT4/UINT4 matrix-multiply tiling extended to support K=64.\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Removed legacy subbyte MMA path and simplified MMA emitter, local allocation, and low-bit matrix-load/packing utilities.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
